---
alwaysApply: true
---

You are an expert in building scalable, maintainable admin panels and SaaS-ready web applications using React 18, Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn-style components, Radix UI, Supabase, and TanStack React Query.

Project Context

Product type: Admin panel with student/teacher portal
Optimization: Internal usage first, SaaS-ready architecture

Tenancy model

Start single-tenant per school

All schemas, IDs, and queries must be designed to support tenant_id in the future

Frontend: React 18 + Vite (NOT Next.js)
Backend: Supabase (Postgres, Auth, RLS, Edge Functions)

Core Principles

Prefer correctness, clarity, and maintainability over clever abstractions

Write production-ready TypeScript with explicit intent

Optimize for team ownership and long-term evolution

Avoid overengineering and framework cargo-culting

Frontend Architecture

Use feature-based structure:

features/
users/
classes/
enrollments/
components/
ui/ (primitives only, shadcn-style)
services/
supabase/
hooks/
storage/

components/ui rules

Treated as read-only primitives

No business logic

No behavioral changes

Only bugfixes are allowed

All composition and behavior must live inside features/*

React & Component Conventions

Use functional components with explicit typing:
const Component: React.FC<Props> = (props) => {}

Prefer interface for props and object shapes

Use type only for unions, aliases, and discriminated unions

Keep components small and focused

Do NOT introduce new global providers without explicit human review

Data Fetching & State Management

All remote data must use TanStack React Query

Supabase access must be wrapped in a service layer
services/supabase/users.ts
services/supabase/classes.ts

Components must NEVER call the Supabase client directly

Expose resource-specific hooks:
useUsersQuery
useCreateUserMutation
useUpdateClassMutation

Mutations

Default behavior: invalidate related queries

Optimistic updates only when UX clearly requires it

Optimistic updates MUST include rollback logic and tests

Do NOT use useEffect for data fetching

Supabase Rules

Use Row Level Security (RLS) for all sensitive tables:
profiles
user_roles
financial_records

RLS policies must be explicit, minimal, and reviewed

Do NOT modify production RLS or policies without human approval

Never expose service-role or admin keys

Privileged actions must be handled via Edge Functions

The agent may propose or implement new Edge Functions only when clearly justified

Forms & Validation

Use react-hook-form for all forms

Use zod at ALL boundaries:
form inputs
API inputs
API outputs

Prefer schema-driven validation

Avoid duplicating validation logic across layers

Testing Standards

Use Vitest + Testing Library

Tests are required for new features and critical bugfixes

Focus on behavior, edge cases, and permission/access boundaries

Avoid shallow snapshot-only tests

Styling & UI

Use Tailwind CSS exclusively for styling

Use clsx, tailwind-merge, and class-variance-authority when needed

Follow Radix + shadcn accessibility patterns

Ensure keyboard navigation and correct ARIA attributes

Storage & Side Effects

Do NOT access localStorage, sessionStorage, or cookies directly

Use abstractions under storage/*

Avoid hidden side effects inside components

Code Quality & Linting

ESLint rules are enforced

Exceptions are allowed ONLY with a clear justification comment and a TODO

Avoid permanent eslint-disable directives

Documentation & Output Rules

DO NOT generate .md files (README, docs, guides, explanations)

Do NOT create documentation-only files unless explicitly requested

Avoid verbose inline comments

Comments must explain why, never what

When implementing something

Just write the code

Respond concisely with what was done

No tutorials, no long explanations

Version Control Rules

The agent MAY perform git commit only on the dev branch

Never commit directly to main, master, or production branches

Always assume dev is the active working branch

Commits must reflect only the changes just implemented

Do NOT include secrets, .env files, or sensitive keys in commits

Forbidden Actions

The agent must NOT:

Create new global providers without review

Fetch data inside components using useEffect

Bypass the Supabase service layer

Modify RLS or production policies without review

Commit secrets or .env files

Expose admin or service-role keys client-side

Generate markdown documentation files by default

Mindset

Design everything as SaaS-ready, even if currently single-tenant

Prefer explicit APIs over magic behavior

Optimize for future contributors

Assume this codebase will grow and be maintained by a team
